00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:50,170
 * Forever and eternally 

254
00:17:50,203 --> 00:17:56,143
 * Sounds heavenly 
 In love to me 

255
00:17:59,312 --> 00:18:02,415
 * Could heaven...  

256
00:18:02,449 --> 00:18:03,650
What's a nice...

257
00:18:03,683 --> 00:18:05,818
May I have the pleasure
to dance with your wife?

258
00:18:05,852 --> 00:18:07,454
Marilyn,
you won first prize.

259
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:21,734
I have a telegram.

260
00:18:21,768 --> 00:18:24,137
Just came from Israel.
Some old friends of mine.

261
00:18:24,171 --> 00:18:25,738
I'd like to
read it to you.

262
00:18:25,772 --> 00:18:27,307
Before Marilyn
gets back.

263
00:18:29,209 --> 00:18:30,710
Here we are.

264
00:18:30,743 --> 00:18:32,745
&quot;There was
a young lady
named Gloria,

265
00:18:34,181 --> 00:18:36,649
who went down on the
Andrea Doria...&quot;

266
00:18:36,683 --> 00:18:39,486
Leon, we got
ladies present.

267
00:18:39,519 --> 00:18:41,421
You've heard
it before.
I know.

268
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:44,624
But you haven't
heard this one.

269
00:18:45,558 --> 00:18:46,593
To a wonderful trip.

270
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:47,494
ALL: Aww!

271
00:18:47,527 --> 00:18:50,230
[RAISING A TOAST
IN A FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

272
00:18:52,199 --> 00:18:54,334
Nice people,
those Americans.

273
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,568
American Jews.

274
00:18:55,602 --> 00:18:56,936
What difference
does that make?

275
00:18:56,969 --> 00:18:59,172
Obviously
none to you.

276
00:18:59,206 --> 00:19:00,740
[LOUD LAUGHTER]

277
00:19:05,878 --> 00:19:08,415
So, you're from
New York City?

278
00:19:08,448 --> 00:19:11,551
Yes, the East Village.
Do you know it?

279
00:19:11,584 --> 00:19:12,819
Oh, yes.

280
00:19:12,852 --> 00:19:15,722
In fact, you could say,
I'm part American, too.

281
00:19:15,755 --> 00:19:19,626
Most of my bothers and sisters
were born in the United States.

282
00:19:19,892 --> 00:19:21,160
Oh.

283
00:19:21,694 --> 00:19:23,530
LADY: Jincia!

284
00:19:23,563 --> 00:19:26,266
Can I dance, too?
Mommy, please?

285
00:19:26,299 --> 00:19:28,768
No, signorina.
You are going straight
to your bed.

286
00:19:28,801 --> 00:19:31,304
Now, Grandma
will tuck you in.

287
00:19:31,338 --> 00:19:32,539
Now be a
good girl.

288
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:36,943
See you
in the morning.

289
00:19:38,878 --> 00:19:40,313
But not
too early.

290
00:19:47,854 --> 00:19:50,457
[APPLAUSE]

291
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:07,540
Hello.
Hi.

292
00:20:07,574 --> 00:20:09,309
Wanna dance?
Okay.

293
00:20:11,511 --> 00:20:12,679
No.

294
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:14,681
Something wrong?
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

295
00:20:14,714 --> 00:20:15,782
I'm a...
What?

296
00:20:15,815 --> 00:20:17,350
Sea sickness.

297
00:20:20,553 --> 00:20:21,588
I'm fine.

298
00:20:27,927 --> 00:20:29,762
[JOVIAL MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:20:32,732 --> 00:20:33,900
Let's dance.

300
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:35,001
No.

301
00:20:39,539 --> 00:20:40,707
Show us
what you can do.

302
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,241
All right.
You asked for it.

303
00:20:45,412 --> 00:20:46,979
Go on. Dance.
Go on.

304
00:20:47,013 --> 00:20:48,415
I'm going.

305
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:10,269
Oh, come on, dance.
Try to enjoy yourself.

306
00:21:10,903 --> 00:21:12,672
How can you
enjoy this?

307
00:21:12,705 --> 00:21:14,374
Everybody else
is doing it.

308
00:21:14,407 --> 00:21:15,775
But not me.
Forget it.

309
00:21:17,777 --> 00:21:19,779
I need some air.
Have fun.

310
00:21:38,665 --> 00:21:39,832
Good evening,
Captain.

311
00:21:39,866 --> 00:21:40,900
Good evening.

312
00:21:42,635 --> 00:21:44,571
What's this?
A komboloi.

313
00:21:44,604 --> 00:21:47,740
A Greek rosary.
To wish you
a pleasant journey.

314
00:21:47,774 --> 00:21:51,644
If I am not mistaken,
we've seen you on the
 Lauro before, Mr...

315
00:21:51,678 --> 00:21:53,646
Petros.
Floros Petros.

316
00:21:54,981 --> 00:21:57,016
You have
a good memory,
Captain De Rosa.

317
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:01,721
Good night.

318
00:22:01,754 --> 00:22:02,955
Good night.

319
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:09,596
[JOVIAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:22:48,635 --> 00:22:51,103
[SOFT, POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]

321
00:23:23,736 --> 00:23:25,672
Where the hell am I?

322
00:23:25,705 --> 00:23:29,141
Ah! It's a beautiful
sunny day.

323
00:23:29,175 --> 00:23:32,479
What a great way
to start a cruise, Leon.

324
00:23:32,512 --> 00:23:34,514
My father
used to say,

325
00:23:34,547 --> 00:23:37,584
&quot;If you wanna sleep in peace
marry a woman with
low blood pressure.&quot;

326
00:23:37,917 --> 00:23:39,519
[LAUGHS]

327
00:23:39,552 --> 00:23:40,820
Come on.

328
00:23:40,853 --> 00:23:42,321
Rise and shine.
Get moving.

329
00:23:42,354 --> 00:23:46,158
You can sleep at home for free.
In here, you're paying for
every minute.

330
00:23:46,192 --> 00:23:47,494
Now, come on.

331
00:23:47,527 --> 00:23:49,061
Get moving.

332
00:23:49,095 --> 00:23:51,731
There's a whole
new world out there, Leon.

333
00:23:51,764 --> 00:23:54,634
Now.
Agh!

334
00:23:54,667 --> 00:23:58,137
Some days I think
this is all a bad dream.

335
00:23:58,170 --> 00:24:01,674
I'll wake up one morning.
Call for the dog.
Go running in the park.

336
00:24:02,675 --> 00:24:04,110
Come on, Leon.
Come on.

337
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:07,547
Come on, pull.
Come on.

338
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:10,149
Where do you think
you're going, young lady?

339
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,184
Come here.

340
00:24:13,886 --> 00:24:15,488
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

341
00:24:16,723 --> 00:24:19,759
Oh! Mmm.

342
00:24:30,670 --> 00:24:32,071
[GUN SHOTS]

343
00:24:33,706 --> 00:24:34,707
Pull.

344
00:24:36,008 --> 00:24:37,610
[GUN SHOT]

345
00:24:37,644 --> 00:24:38,645
Pull.

346
00:24:39,546 --> 00:24:41,080
[GUN SHOT]

347
00:24:41,113 --> 00:24:42,515
[PIERRE SPEAKS FRENCH]

348
00:24:42,549 --> 00:24:43,916
MAN: Yeah, not bad.
Not bad.

349
00:24:45,885 --> 00:24:46,886
Pull.

350
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:49,556
[GUN SHOT]

351
00:24:49,589 --> 00:24:50,590
Pull.

352
00:24:51,958 --> 00:24:53,626
Ah!

353
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:54,894
[APPLAUSE]

354
00:24:54,927 --> 00:24:57,296
Did you see that?
Yeah, we showed them.

355
00:24:57,329 --> 00:24:58,731
[LAUGHTER]

356
00:24:58,765 --> 00:25:01,167
Your turn, Stead.
Let's get out of here.

357
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,702
We two haven't
finished yet.

358
00:25:02,735 --> 00:25:04,070
Ah, but I
have to leave.

359
00:25:04,103 --> 00:25:05,738
Hey, Leon,
where're you going?

360
00:25:05,772 --> 00:25:07,540
You want us
to lose the war?

361
00:25:07,574 --> 00:25:09,976
Oh, dear. [SIGHS]

362
00:25:10,009 --> 00:25:11,911
You're tired, sir?
Is that why you stop?

363
00:25:11,944 --> 00:25:13,913
No, no. Just quit
while you are ahead.

364
00:25:13,946 --> 00:25:18,217
I might make another
double like that,
if I live to be a thousand.

365
00:25:18,250 --> 00:25:20,687
You're only joking, sir.
You're a wonderful shooter.

366
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:22,955
Wonderful shot?
You should've seen me
during the war.

367
00:25:22,989 --> 00:25:24,290
You ever heard of
Pearl Harbor.

368
00:25:24,323 --> 00:25:26,192
You were there, sir?
Well, just move over

369
00:25:26,225 --> 00:25:27,694
and I'll show you
what I did.

370
00:25:27,727 --> 00:25:32,765
I was the first one on my ship
to see those Jap zeros
coming down on our ship.

371
00:25:32,799 --> 00:25:34,834
I ran to the bridge,
I got the machine gun,

372
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:36,302
I began firing
at them right away.

373
00:25:36,335 --> 00:25:37,970
[MAKING MACHINE GUN NOISES]

374
00:25:38,004 --> 00:25:39,305
[LAUGHTER]

375
00:25:39,338 --> 00:25:41,240
I got two of the bastards
before I was hit.

376
00:25:41,273 --> 00:25:43,342
So you are a hero
of the war?

377
00:25:43,375 --> 00:25:46,679
[LAUGHS] No, Ferrari.
I'm only kidding.

378
00:25:46,713 --> 00:25:49,281
I was wounded
in New York City's
combat zone.

379
00:25:49,315 --> 00:25:51,050
But that was
after the war.

380
00:25:51,083 --> 00:25:54,253
I was hit in the heart
by cigarettes, booze,
cholesterol.

381
00:25:55,154 --> 00:25:56,222
You name it.

382
00:26:00,627 --> 00:26:01,928
You know,
fate's a funny girl.

383
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:05,898
Too bad, she couldn't have
finished the job.

384
00:26:05,932 --> 00:26:08,901
Oh, no sir. You must
never talk like this.

385
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:13,740
For me it is enough
to be alive.

386
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:16,776
Blind or deaf...

387
00:26:16,809 --> 00:26:19,145
Even without arms,
or legs is...

388
00:26:20,713 --> 00:26:21,948
Without anything.

389
00:26:29,956 --> 00:26:33,125
Well, maybe not
without anything.

390
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:34,861
But, uh...

391
00:26:36,062 --> 00:26:37,730
No. No. Maybe not.

392
00:26:39,265 --> 00:26:40,599
You have
a beautiful wife.

393
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,903
She loves you
very much.

394
00:26:43,936 --> 00:26:47,206
You can see it.
She's always looking
to be sure you are there.

395
00:26:47,239 --> 00:26:49,041
Like she's almost afraid
to not find you.

396
00:26:52,712 --> 00:26:54,681
Sorry, sir.
Have I said
something wrong.

397
00:26:55,381 --> 00:26:57,049
Oh, you're a good kid,
Ferrari.

398
00:27:01,954 --> 00:27:04,824
I must remember
to make our bookings.

399
00:27:04,857 --> 00:27:06,392
We don't want
to miss the Pyramids.

400
00:27:06,425 --> 00:27:09,361
You're joking.
Arabs, smells...

401
00:27:09,395 --> 00:27:11,097
Filth, camels.

402
00:27:11,130 --> 00:27:13,032
No, it's not
for me, Margo.

403
00:27:13,065 --> 00:27:14,400
Not for me.

404
00:27:14,433 --> 00:27:17,103
But it is for me, Pierre.
And I don't care whether
you come or not.

405
00:27:17,136 --> 00:27:18,771
What's the matter
with you?

406
00:27:18,805 --> 00:27:20,840
How kind of you
to finally ask.

407
00:27:24,844 --> 00:27:27,013
I have brought up
three children for you.

408
00:27:27,046 --> 00:27:29,949
I have given you
my love and loyalty.

409
00:27:29,982 --> 00:27:34,220
I have put up with your
existential crisis
and your affairs.

410
00:27:34,253 --> 00:27:36,288
For 20 years
I have permitted you

411
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:38,190
to teach me things
I know better than you.

412
00:27:39,391 --> 00:27:40,727
[WAITER SPEAKS ITALIAN]

413
00:27:41,728 --> 00:27:43,062
 Perfecto. 

414
00:27:44,463 --> 00:27:46,398
This cruise
was not so much a gift,

415
00:27:46,432 --> 00:27:49,368
as a sort of bone you threw
to me to keep me quiet.

416
00:27:50,302 --> 00:27:51,370
I knew that.

417
00:27:52,238 --> 00:27:53,873
What is the
matter with me?

418
00:27:54,874 --> 00:27:57,143
Maybe I'm tired
of you, Pierre.

419
00:27:59,011 --> 00:28:00,679
Or maybe
I'm tired of us.

420
00:28:03,850 --> 00:28:06,185
I shall be
thinking about it
at the Pyramids.

421
00:28:10,757 --> 00:28:11,824
You always say no.

422
00:28:11,858 --> 00:28:13,459
[LAUGHTER]

423
00:28:13,492 --> 00:28:15,194
Don't worry.
I'll save you!

424
00:28:15,227 --> 00:28:16,462
[SPLASH]

425
00:28:16,963 --> 00:28:18,030
Oh!

426
00:28:19,265 --> 00:28:20,299
Hi.

427
00:28:20,833 --> 00:28:21,934
Hi.

428
00:28:23,870 --> 00:28:25,704
Come back.
Where are you going?

429
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:29,475
Listen, Cheryl,
if you like,

430
00:28:29,508 --> 00:28:32,745
later we can all go together
to see the Pyramids.

431
00:28:32,779 --> 00:28:33,913
No, I've
seen them.

432
00:28:33,946 --> 00:28:35,181
You two go.

433
00:28:35,214 --> 00:28:36,415
Are you
mad at me?

434
00:28:36,949 --> 00:28:37,984
Cheryl!

435
00:28:50,162 --> 00:28:51,497
I need some
time alone, anyway.

436
00:28:53,265 --> 00:28:54,266
I get it.

437
00:28:55,101 --> 00:28:56,202
It is me.

438
00:28:57,970 --> 00:28:59,105
I just
need to think.

439
00:28:59,138 --> 00:29:00,139
Fine.

440
00:29:03,309 --> 00:29:04,911
No, Helmut,

441
00:29:05,444 --> 00:29:06,445
I like you.

442
00:29:07,980 --> 00:29:09,015
I do.

443
00:29:11,317 --> 00:29:13,485
Hey! What
about me?

444
00:29:15,454 --> 00:29:20,226
You too, Michele.
Maybe that's the...
I don't know...

445
00:29:20,259 --> 00:29:22,995
Listen, I have an idea.
Today you will
spend it with Helmut,

446
00:29:23,029 --> 00:29:24,931
and tomorrow
with me.

447
00:29:24,964 --> 00:29:26,332
But I don't see
how that could...

448
00:29:26,365 --> 00:29:29,535
Oh, the best man wins.
I love it.

449
00:29:30,336 --> 00:29:31,337
Oh, I don't.

450
00:29:32,538 --> 00:29:33,806
It is not
a game.

451
00:29:46,218 --> 00:29:48,254
When the tourists
disembark in Alexandria,

452
00:29:48,287 --> 00:29:50,356
I will leave the ship
at the very last moment.

453
00:29:50,389 --> 00:29:52,558
Pretending
to be worried.

454
00:29:52,591 --> 00:29:54,426
When the boys ask
what has happened,

455
00:29:54,460 --> 00:29:57,363
you will say,
&quot;The steward came
into the cabin

456
00:29:57,396 --> 00:30:00,099
and saw the weapons.&quot;
That's what you suspect.

457
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:02,234
So you must take
immediate action.

458
00:30:02,268 --> 00:30:04,170
Or you will be
captured.

459
00:30:04,203 --> 00:30:05,571
I hope they
believe me.

460
00:30:07,206 --> 00:30:08,574
Even Arafat
will believe you.

461
00:30:11,477 --> 00:30:15,447
 Alena, my love, 
 there are so many things 
 I would like to tell you. 

462
00:30:16,448 --> 00:30:18,617
 But I'm here 
 only to fight. 

463
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:21,187
 And that's how I want you 
 to remember me. 

464
00:30:22,889 --> 00:30:24,423
 Sometimes I dream 
 of the day 

465
00:30:24,456 --> 00:30:27,059
 when I'll be able 
 to shake an Israeli's hand. 

466
00:30:27,093 --> 00:30:29,328
 Look into his eyes 
 and say, 

467
00:30:29,361 --> 00:30:31,898
 &quot;Let's stop fighting. 
 Let's find a solution.&quot; 

468
00:30:33,032 --> 00:30:35,101
 But it's not possible. 

469
00:30:35,134 --> 00:30:38,037
 We want everything 
 and so do they. 

470
00:30:38,070 --> 00:30:40,372
 For us, 
 there is no country 
 called Israel. 

471
00:30:40,406 --> 00:30:44,276
 There is only Palestine. 
 And he day after tomorrow, 
 I will be there. 

472
00:30:44,310 --> 00:30:46,245
 And I will fight 
 our enemy. 

473
00:30:46,278 --> 00:30:47,880
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

474
00:30:47,914 --> 00:30:50,116
MAN: Bedding service.
Can we make the beds?

475
00:30:50,149 --> 00:30:51,550
No, thank you.

476
00:30:51,583 --> 00:30:53,052
MAN: Do you need
some towels?

477
00:30:54,353 --> 00:30:55,554
I said,
&quot;No, thank you.&quot;

478
00:30:57,189 --> 00:30:58,324
It's not necessary.

479
00:31:00,226 --> 00:31:02,394
Ah! Less work
for me.

480
00:31:02,428 --> 00:31:05,031
I've been trained to clean up
big stations with standard.

481
00:31:05,064 --> 00:31:06,899
To hell with them.
[SPEAKS ITALIAN]

482
00:31:07,433 --> 00:31:09,168
[MUMBLING IN ITALIAN]

483
00:31:31,057 --> 00:31:33,559
[SHIP HORN HOOTING]

484
00:31:35,694 --> 00:31:39,198
MAN: Mr. Petros, I have your
photographs and your negatives.

485
00:31:39,231 --> 00:31:40,933
Thank you,
very much.

486
00:31:40,967 --> 00:31:42,134
MAN: Okay.
Thank you, sir.

487
00:31:42,168 --> 00:31:44,036
You have my card
if you need anything else.

488
00:31:46,305 --> 00:31:48,307
[WAVES SPLASHING]

489
00:32:14,166 --> 00:32:16,969
So, you'll be
a good girl, huh?

490
00:32:17,003 --> 00:32:18,704
And do as your
Grandma tell you, okay?

491
00:32:18,737 --> 00:32:20,406
Yes, Mummy.

492
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:22,008
We'll be
back tomorrow.

493
00:32:22,041 --> 00:32:23,475
I wish you
were coming, too, Mama.

494
00:32:23,509 --> 00:32:27,113
No. No. I will be
just fine with Jincia.

495
00:32:27,146 --> 00:32:28,214
Don't worry.

496
00:32:28,247 --> 00:32:29,515
Goodbye.
Enjoy yourself.

497
00:32:29,548 --> 00:32:31,650
Daddy!
Thank you.

498
00:32:31,683 --> 00:32:35,154
Oh, I appreciate it so much,
Mama. You'll never know, really.

499
00:32:35,187 --> 00:32:36,722
I know. I know.
Bye, Mama.

500
00:32:36,755 --> 00:32:38,290
Bye bye.
Bye bye, baby.

501
00:32:39,358 --> 00:32:42,294
We'll see you
tomorrow in Port Said.

502
00:32:42,328 --> 00:32:43,562
Bye bye.

503
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:47,166
[BELLS SOUNDING FAINTLY]

504
00:32:56,742 --> 00:32:58,044
ANTONIO: We're over here.

505
00:33:04,083 --> 00:33:05,651
I wish she didn't
insist on going.

506
00:33:07,253 --> 00:33:08,687
The sun is murder.

507
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:16,328
Cover yourself
with that scarf.

508
00:33:17,229 --> 00:33:18,630
Put it on your neck.
Okay.

509
00:33:18,664 --> 00:33:20,032
Okay, I go.

510
00:33:20,066 --> 00:33:21,100
Thank you,
Antonio.

511
00:33:21,133 --> 00:33:22,168
Enjoy your day.

512
00:33:22,201 --> 00:33:23,469
See you tomorrow
in Port Said.

513
00:33:26,805 --> 00:33:28,574
LEON: Oh, dear.
It's warm.

514
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:32,178
LEON: Not so
fast, Marilyn.

515
00:33:32,811 --> 00:33:33,879
LEON: Not so fast.

516
00:33:33,912 --> 00:33:36,282
MARILYN: What's the matter,
Leon? You all right?

517
00:33:36,315 --> 00:33:37,449
LEON: I'm all right.

518
00:33:37,483 --> 00:33:40,519
LEON: All this noise
and confusion.

519
00:33:40,552 --> 00:33:43,189
MARILYN: Look, honey.
We don't have to go.

520
00:33:43,222 --> 00:33:46,058
I mean, it might be too tiring.

521
00:33:46,092 --> 00:33:47,126
LEON: Listen, darling.

522
00:33:47,159 --> 00:33:48,260
You can't come to...

523
00:33:48,294 --> 00:33:51,630
You can't come to Egypt
and not go to see the Pyramids

524
00:33:51,663 --> 00:33:53,299
and the Sphinx.

525
00:33:53,332 --> 00:33:54,566
Quit fussing.

526
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:57,669
Look, Leon. I think you're going
because you think I wanna go.

527
00:33:57,703 --> 00:34:00,839
I mean, I-I-I couldn't give
a damn. All I want
is to be with you.

528
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:02,174
Oh, God.

529
00:34:03,175 --> 00:34:04,376
I don't know
what I wanna do.

530
00:34:05,577 --> 00:34:08,714
Okay, Leon,
we're gonna go back
to the ship.

531
00:34:12,451 --> 00:34:13,485
Your guests won't mind.

532
00:34:13,519 --> 00:34:15,287
Wait a minute,
I'm all right.

533
00:34:15,321 --> 00:34:17,256
Leon we're gonna
go back to the ship.

534
00:34:17,289 --> 00:34:19,258
I think
it's best.

535
00:34:19,291 --> 00:34:21,560
Now, let's just take
one day at a time.

536
00:34:24,863 --> 00:34:27,299
Look, we'll just
keep the Cohens company.

537
00:34:27,333 --> 00:34:28,334
Oh.
Okay?

538
00:34:43,382 --> 00:34:44,683
Marilyn,
over here!

539
00:34:45,851 --> 00:34:48,754
Rose, we're gonna
take a rain check.

540
00:34:49,888 --> 00:34:52,291
So, you have
a great time.

541
00:34:52,324 --> 00:34:53,859
We'll see you tomorrow
at Port Said.

542
00:34:55,527 --> 00:34:58,330
Don't worry.
We'll bring you
a nice souvenir.

543
00:34:59,165 --> 00:35:00,699
Bring back
a belly dancer.

544
00:35:01,700 --> 00:35:03,101
[BUS DOOR SWISHES SHUT]

545
00:35:04,836 --> 00:35:08,607
I thought they
were dying to see
the Pyramids.

546
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:11,243
Poor Marilyn. She really
doesn't look too well.

547
00:35:11,510 --> 00:35:12,511
What?

548
00:35:14,380 --> 00:35:16,415
Look, I don't wanna
talk about it.

549
00:35:16,448 --> 00:35:18,850
Today's our day.
Let's have a good time,
okay?

550
00:35:18,884 --> 00:35:21,487
You're right.
To hell with Leon.

551
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,822
If I find a belly dancer,
I'll keep her for myself.

552
00:35:23,855 --> 00:35:24,890
You would.

553
00:35:24,923 --> 00:35:26,124
[CHUCKLES]

554
00:35:53,352 --> 00:35:55,954
I am sorry I'm late.
But I must go ashore.

555
00:35:55,987 --> 00:35:59,258
But you are not
on the list for the tour,
Mr. Petros.

556
00:35:59,291 --> 00:36:02,228
No, I'm afraid
I have to leave
this beautiful cruise.

557
00:36:02,261 --> 00:36:03,462
PETROS: My wife is sick.

558
00:36:04,963 --> 00:36:08,267
No, no, I already
have my passport.

559
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,501
LADY: All right, go ahead.

560
00:36:09,535 --> 00:36:11,237
Thank you.
 Shukr. 

561
00:36:15,407 --> 00:36:18,210
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

562
00:36:49,941 --> 00:36:50,942
[DOOR OPENS]

563
00:36:51,977 --> 00:36:53,512
What's going on?

564
00:36:53,545 --> 00:36:55,481
I just saw Petros
leaving the ship now.

565
00:36:55,514 --> 00:36:58,750
We've been found out.
I believe a steward
saw the arms.

566
00:37:00,852 --> 00:37:01,987
He can't have.

567
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:04,490
I'm telling you, he did.
He saw us.

568
00:37:04,523 --> 00:37:06,625
If he had, they would have
arrested us by now.

569
00:37:06,658 --> 00:37:07,759
Shut up.

570
00:37:07,793 --> 00:37:10,796
I am the leader,
and I tell you
we have no choice,

571
00:37:10,829 --> 00:37:12,398
but to hijack this ship.

572
00:37:13,699 --> 00:37:15,000
It's crazy.

573
00:37:16,935 --> 00:37:18,670
This is not our plan.

574
00:37:18,704 --> 00:37:20,572
I have a new plan.

575
00:37:20,606 --> 00:37:22,974
You mean,
just the four
of us, alone?

576
00:37:23,008 --> 00:37:24,376
On such
a big ship?

577
00:37:24,410 --> 00:37:27,946
That is why,
they will never know how many
of us there really is.

578
00:37:30,549 --> 00:37:32,651
Well.

579
00:37:32,684 --> 00:37:34,686
There aren't so many
passengers aboard now.

580
00:37:35,621 --> 00:37:36,822
So,
we can
do it?

581
00:37:36,855 --> 00:37:37,889
For what?

582
00:37:39,325 --> 00:37:40,626
And why
an Italian ship?

583
00:37:42,561 --> 00:37:44,663
Huh? Why?

584
00:37:44,696 --> 00:37:47,366
It's Israel who
we must fight.

585
00:37:47,399 --> 00:37:50,402
We are to free
our brothers.

586
00:37:50,436 --> 00:37:53,739
What difference does it make
whether we make our stand
from here

587
00:37:53,772 --> 00:37:55,307
or from Israel?

588
00:37:55,341 --> 00:37:57,909
I am a soldier,

589
00:37:57,943 --> 00:38:01,847
and I don't want to fight
against unarmed people.

590
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:04,350
For us they are
our enemies.

591
00:38:04,383 --> 00:38:05,451
All of them.

592
00:38:08,754 --> 00:38:10,522
We are
at war, brother.

593
00:38:25,904 --> 00:38:27,839
[SHIP HORN HOOTING]

594
00:38:49,127 --> 00:38:50,629
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

595
00:38:52,898 --> 00:38:54,032
[KNOCK AT DOOR]

596
00:38:54,833 --> 00:38:55,967
Who is it?

597
00:38:57,403 --> 00:38:58,870
[KNOCKING CONTINUES]

598
00:39:08,013 --> 00:39:09,881
I thought I wouldn't
see you again.

599
00:39:10,982 --> 00:39:12,350
Well...

600
00:39:13,652 --> 00:39:14,886
I couldn't
stay away.

601
00:39:16,888 --> 00:39:18,023
I'm glad.

602
00:39:19,791 --> 00:39:21,860
But I'm
also still...

603
00:39:23,094 --> 00:39:24,596
I'll see you
in the restaurant.

604
00:39:25,664 --> 00:39:26,798
I'll be
waiting.

605
00:39:32,037 --> 00:39:36,007
MICHELE: So, first round
is yours.

606
00:39:38,744 --> 00:39:41,580
Come on,
I'll buy you
a champagne.

607
00:39:41,613 --> 00:39:43,982
Thank you.
But the next round
is mine.

608
00:39:46,685 --> 00:39:48,086
[SPLASHING]

609
00:39:51,823 --> 00:39:55,794
ANNOUNCER: Ladies 
 and gentlemen, tomorrow 
 we will reach Port Said. 

610
00:39:55,827 --> 00:39:58,497
 Those of you who wish 
 to visit the city, 

611
00:39:58,530 --> 00:40:00,499
 please contact 
 the purser's office. 

612
00:40:00,532 --> 00:40:01,533
 Thank you. 

613
00:40:04,169 --> 00:40:06,638
[ANNOUNCEMENT IN ITALIAN]

614
00:40:15,547 --> 00:40:18,784
[ANNOUNCEMENT IN FRENCH]

615
00:40:20,085 --> 00:40:21,953
[LAUGHTER]

616
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:31,797
[GUN SHOTS BEING FIRED]

617
00:40:50,081 --> 00:40:51,182
Come.

618
00:40:52,818 --> 00:40:54,886
[GUNSHOTS]

619
00:40:56,121 --> 00:40:57,589
On the floor!

620
00:41:08,233 --> 00:41:12,804
ANNOUNCER: Captain De Rosa 
 is requested 
 on the bridge at once. 

621
00:41:12,838 --> 00:41:15,006
 Captain De Rosa 
 on the bridge at once. 

622
00:41:17,743 --> 00:41:18,844
Captain
What's going on?

623
00:41:18,877 --> 00:41:20,512
Someone is firing
the machine gun!

624
00:41:20,546 --> 00:41:21,647
What?
Yes!

625
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:23,649
And shouts are coming
from the restaurant.

626
00:41:23,682 --> 00:41:25,116
Oh, my God.

627
00:41:25,150 --> 00:41:26,585
Put your
uniform on.

628
00:41:26,618 --> 00:41:27,986
Yes, sir.

629
00:41:28,019 --> 00:41:29,487
[GUN SHOTS FIRING]

630
00:41:30,789 --> 00:41:32,257
TERRORIST:
On the floor.
On the floor.

631
00:41:34,726 --> 00:41:36,728
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

632
00:41:41,933 --> 00:41:43,869
TERRORIST:
Back on the bridge,
who's marking?

633
00:41:43,902 --> 00:41:44,936
Now.

634
00:41:46,672 --> 00:41:47,773
Yeah.

635
00:41:52,043 --> 00:41:53,178
What happened?

636
00:41:53,211 --> 00:41:54,312
How many
are they?

637
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:55,581
[CRYING]

638
00:41:55,614 --> 00:41:56,782
Are you hurt?
Huh?

639
00:42:03,254 --> 00:42:05,090
Move.
Everybody.

640
00:42:08,827 --> 00:42:13,031
[MACHINE GUN FIRING]

641
00:42:14,132 --> 00:42:15,133
Fire!

642
00:42:31,683 --> 00:42:35,954
Captain, we are taking this ship
in the name of Arafat's PLO.

643
00:42:35,987 --> 00:42:38,223
We have nothing
against the Italians.

644
00:42:38,256 --> 00:42:39,991
But anybody who
tries to stop us,

645
00:42:40,025 --> 00:42:41,092
will be killed.

646
00:42:42,628 --> 00:42:45,263
We will blow up
this whole ship.

647
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:46,965
There are many
of us, understand?

648
00:42:49,034 --> 00:42:50,501
Yes.

649
00:42:50,535 --> 00:42:53,939
But you've got to understand
that we have more than
300 people on this ship.

650
00:42:55,073 --> 00:42:56,642
There is bound
to be panic.

651
00:42:58,744 --> 00:43:00,311
I'll do
what I can.

652
00:43:03,715 --> 00:43:08,186
But your men...
have to keep
very, very calm.

653
00:43:08,219 --> 00:43:10,188
My men
are soldiers.

654
00:43:11,890 --> 00:43:13,792
Stop the ship,
now.

655
00:43:18,964 --> 00:43:20,098
Stop
the engines.

656
00:43:20,999 --> 00:43:22,133
Move.

657
00:43:29,841 --> 00:43:31,042
MAN: Captain.

658
00:43:45,056 --> 00:43:48,159
CAPTAIN: Attention please. 
 Your attention, please. 

659
00:43:48,193 --> 00:43:50,228
 This is Captain De Rosa 
 speaking. 

660
00:43:50,261 --> 00:43:53,732
 All passengers 
 and crew members, 

661
00:43:53,765 --> 00:43:57,903
 the ship has been taken over 
 by a group of Palestinians. 

662
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:00,772
 We are no longer underway. 

663
00:44:01,807 --> 00:44:04,409
 I ask that you 
 all remain calm. 

664
00:44:04,442 --> 00:44:06,377
 No one is to 
 take any action. 

665
00:44:06,411 --> 00:44:09,314
 It might endanger his life. 
 And the life of others. 

666
00:44:09,347 --> 00:44:11,449
[SPEAKING IN ARABIC]

667
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:13,752
 Please proceed 
 to the dining area. 

668
00:44:13,785 --> 00:44:18,724
Don't be afraid.

669
00:44:18,757 --> 00:44:21,960
 Proceed to the 
 dining hall at once. 

670
00:44:23,361 --> 00:44:27,132
[CAPTAIN SPEAKING IN ITALIAN]

671
00:44:42,981 --> 00:44:46,084
[ANNOUNCING THE
SAME MESSAGE IN FRENCH]

672
00:45:14,012 --> 00:45:16,447
 This is the 
 Captain speaking. 

673
00:45:16,481 --> 00:45:19,150
 If we follow 
 instructions carefully, 

674
00:45:19,184 --> 00:45:21,119
 nothing will 
 happen to us. 

675
00:45:21,152 --> 00:45:22,720
 I assure you. 

676
00:45:22,754 --> 00:45:27,959
 All passengers and off duty 
 crew members who are 
 still in their cabins 

677
00:45:27,993 --> 00:45:29,795
 in the after part 
 of the ship, 

678
00:45:29,828 --> 00:45:32,730
 must proceed immediately 
 to the main dining hall. 

679
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:39,070
 Passengers and crew members in 
 the after part of the ship... 

680
00:45:39,104 --> 00:45:40,471
TERRORIST: All right.
Stop. Stop.

681
00:45:41,539 --> 00:45:43,809
TERRORIST:
Stop. Nobody move.

682
00:45:45,043 --> 00:45:47,478
TERRORIST:
Everybody down.
Right where you are.

683
00:45:47,512 --> 00:45:48,880
TERRORIST: Go on.

684
00:45:51,582 --> 00:45:53,184
TERRORIST: Don't you
hear me?

685
00:45:54,052 --> 00:45:55,253
TERRORIST:
I said, down.

686
00:45:58,123 --> 00:45:59,357
Keep quiet.

687
00:46:04,195 --> 00:46:05,763
[SPEAKING IN A
FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

688
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:11,269
CAPTAIN: So much
for our artillery.

689
00:46:11,302 --> 00:46:13,471
MAN: [WHISPERING]
No, still have
a gun in my cabin.

690
00:46:13,504 --> 00:46:15,373
If I can find an excuse
to go and get it.

691
00:46:15,406 --> 00:46:17,242
CAPTAIN:
And then what?

692
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:19,878
Suppose they've
really planted
their explosives?

693
00:46:19,911 --> 00:46:22,948
Look, we don't even
know how many they are.

694
00:46:22,981 --> 00:46:26,451
What you need here
is some brain work.

695
00:46:33,191 --> 00:46:34,559
They're only
young boys.

696
00:46:36,294 --> 00:46:39,397
We've got to try
and reason with them.

697
00:46:39,430 --> 00:46:42,100
We've got to
get out of this mess.

698
00:46:42,133 --> 00:46:45,203
Without
any more shooting.

699
00:46:45,236 --> 00:46:47,805
TERRORIST: Walkie talkie.
You have walkie talkie?

700
00:46:49,374 --> 00:46:50,541
Hand them out.

701
00:47:00,251 --> 00:47:01,920
Take it.

702
00:47:07,092 --> 00:47:08,159
Do you hear me?

703
00:47:09,127 --> 00:47:11,362
-Hello?
-I hear you.

704
00:47:20,538 --> 00:47:22,307
Up. Up.

705
00:47:23,508 --> 00:47:25,443
Move. Move.
Get up. Get up.

706
00:47:30,548 --> 00:47:32,517
Move. Faster.
Faster. Go on.

707
00:47:32,550 --> 00:47:34,252
Move everybody,
move.

708
00:47:34,285 --> 00:47:35,586
CAPTAIN: No, no, no, no.

709
00:47:35,620 --> 00:47:37,188
My second
in command,

710
00:47:37,956 --> 00:47:39,324
my radio operator.

711
00:47:39,357 --> 00:47:42,427
And the bridge staff
 must stay here.

712
00:47:49,634 --> 00:47:51,202
Keep your eye on them.

713
00:47:57,175 --> 00:47:58,309
Okay.

714
00:47:59,344 --> 00:48:00,678
Everybody, out.
Out.

715
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:02,613
Do what
they ask.

716
00:48:02,647 --> 00:48:04,215
And nobody
will get hurt.

717
00:48:12,623 --> 00:48:14,325
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

718
00:48:16,361 --> 00:48:17,595
[COUGHING]

719
00:48:26,604 --> 00:48:28,306
TERRORIST: The Captain
comes with me.

720
00:48:28,339 --> 00:48:30,241
TERRORIST: The rest
of you stay here.

721
00:48:30,275 --> 00:48:32,243
TERRORIST: Go on.
Go on.

722
00:48:35,246 --> 00:48:37,015
Be calm.

723
00:48:37,048 --> 00:48:39,384
Keep calm.
Nothing will happen
if you keep calm.

724
00:48:39,417 --> 00:48:40,685
Get all of them
to the ball room.

725
00:48:40,718 --> 00:48:42,587
I want everybody
in the ball room now.

726
00:48:42,620 --> 00:48:44,722
But the ball room
is on the upper deck.

727
00:48:44,755 --> 00:48:46,291
I know that.

728
00:48:46,324 --> 00:48:49,094
It means we move
these people
through this ship.

729
00:48:49,127 --> 00:48:50,361
Will you
shut up?

730
00:48:50,395 --> 00:48:53,331
You have enough men,
to make sure
there are no incidents?

731
00:48:53,364 --> 00:48:55,433
You're trying
to be clever.
I'm on to you.

732
00:48:55,466 --> 00:48:57,468
TERRORIST:
We have the whole ship
under control.

733
00:48:58,736 --> 00:49:01,072
[GUNSHOTS]

734
00:49:03,308 --> 00:49:05,476
[PEOPLE SCREAMING IN PANIC]

735
00:49:05,510 --> 00:49:06,711
TERRORIST: Assadi!

736
00:49:10,015 --> 00:49:11,516
[GUN FIRING]

737
00:49:18,789 --> 00:49:21,126
[GUN SHOTS]

738
00:49:21,159 --> 00:49:22,327
TERRORISTS: Go. Go.
Go. Go.

739
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:24,095
[GUN SHOTS]

740
00:49:25,130 --> 00:49:27,132
[SCREAMING] Go.
Take him out.

741
00:49:27,565 --> 00:49:28,599
Go!

742
00:49:29,567 --> 00:49:32,070
[PEOPLE SCREAMING
IN PANIC]

743
00:49:32,103 --> 00:49:33,138
[GUNSHOTS]

744
00:49:34,772 --> 00:49:36,007
TERRORIST: Move!

745
00:49:42,613 --> 00:49:43,948
Keep calm.

746
00:49:43,981 --> 00:49:46,684
How can you let them
herd us sheep?
Why don't your men do something?

747
00:49:46,717 --> 00:49:48,586
This is not
a warship, sir.

748
00:49:48,619 --> 00:49:52,290
And my crew
is mostly clerks
and stewards.

749
00:49:52,323 --> 00:49:54,159
This way,
calmly.

750
00:49:54,192 --> 00:49:55,626
Calmly, please.

751
00:49:55,660 --> 00:49:57,028
CAPTAIN: Calmly.

752
00:49:57,062 --> 00:49:58,196
TERRORIST: Go, go.

753
00:50:04,535 --> 00:50:05,670
TERRORIST: Move, move.

754
00:50:08,406 --> 00:50:09,440
TERRORIST: Come on.

755
00:50:10,575 --> 00:50:11,742
LADY: Help me.

756
00:50:11,776 --> 00:50:13,144
Come on.

757
00:50:13,178 --> 00:50:16,281
Cheryl. She must hiding
in the cabin. We got
to get her before he does.

758
00:50:16,314 --> 00:50:17,382
Oh, wait,
wait, wait.

759
00:50:20,285 --> 00:50:21,486
TERRORIST: Move. Move.

760
00:50:21,519 --> 00:50:23,821
LADY: Peter. Peter.

761
00:50:23,854 --> 00:50:25,356
TERRORIST:
